column3: Formpro Ratings Free Every Monday C0

column5: Owned/Raced by: Sparkle and Fade Syndicate
column7: Trained by: B D F Craik

column1: ARIANA SUNSET (1) - bumped BIG TIME ROONIE on several occasions through the back straight. Tightened entering the bend. Bumped BIG TIME JOEY on the point of the bend, becoming unbalanced and losing ground. Raced wide through the home straight.

BIG TIME ROONIE (3) - bumped on several occasions through the back straight. Tightened ARIANA SUNSET entering the bend. Tightened ALLEGRO KYLE nearing the home straight. Tightened entering the home straight, needing to check off heels as a result.
BIG TIME JOEY (5) - bumped at the start. Bumped JACK MARJEN shortly after the start. Tightened JACK MARJEN entering the bend. Tightened BIG TIME KEVIN and BIG TIME ROONIE entering the home straight.
PORTLAND BERTY (6) - bumped at the start.
BIG TIME KEVIN (7) - slow away. Awkwardly placed behind runners nearing the bend. Tightened entering the home straight.
ALLEGRO KYLE (9/8) - bumped PORTLAND BERTY at the start.

JACK MARJEN (10/2) - bumped shortly after the start. Tightened entering the bend, becoming very unbalanced and losing ground, failed to get back into contention thereafter. A post race veterinary examination was carried out which revealed no injuries.

column3: Aaron White Calling Here March 16th C1/C2

column1: TUFF TEMPTRESS (1) - bumped then tightened entering the bend. Raced wide through the home straight.
BARBAROSSA BOY (2) - bumped then tightened TUFF TEMPTRESS entering the bend.
BIG TIME DUSTY (3) - bumped BIGTIME KATE at the start.
BIGTIME KATE (4) - bumped at the start.
PARIS END (6) - slow away. Bumped entering the bend.

BIGTIME RONNIE (9/5) - awkwardly placed behind runners shortly after the start, needing to check off heels as a result. Bumped PARIS END entering the bend, becoming momentarily unbalanced and losing ground. A post race veterinary examination was carried out which revealed no injuries.

column3: Auckland Railway Sprint Heats 23rd February C3/C4

column1: BIGTIME BANJO (3) - raced wide through the home straight.

BIG TIME SPOT (4) - tightened at the start, needing to check off heels. Moved up the track and squeezed BIGTIME LEADS shortly after the start. Jostled with BIGTIME LIZZY nearing the bend. Raced wide through the home straight.
HARPOON HARRY (5) - tightened BIG TIME SPOT at the start.
BIGTIME LEADS (6) - squeezed between runners shortly after the start, losing ground as a result.
BIGTIME LIZZY (7) - squeezed BIGTIME LEADS shortly after the start. Jostled with BIG TIME SPOT nearing the bend. Tightened on the point of the bend. Raced wide through the home straight.
BIG TIME GWYN (8) - tightened BIGTIME LIZZY on the point of the bend.
BIG TIME DYNASTY (1) - inconvenienced BILLY'S CHURN entering the bend when moving up the track. Bumped from behind nearing the home straight.
BIG TIME CLARE (2) - raced wide through the home straight.
BIG TIME LEBRON (3) - raced wide through the home straight.
BILLY'S CHURN (4) - inconvenienced entering the bend, losing momentum as a result.

BEES AND BIRDS (6) - brushed BIG TIME PLUTO shortly after the start. Checked from behind entering the bend, stumbling and falling. Regained her feet and completed the event. Raced wide through the home straight. A post race veterinary examination was carried out which revealed no injuries.
BIG TIME PLUTO (7) - brushed BEES AND BIRDS shortly after the start.
DYNAMITE DANGER (8) - checked BEES AND BIRDS from behind entering the bend.
DIAMOND GEEZER (1) - squeezed CLASSIC RAPPER shortly after the start. Tightened entering the bend, needing to check off heels to gain clear racing room. Raced wide through the home straight.

CLASSIC RAPPER (2) - squeezed between runners shortly after the start, losing a considerable amount of ground and never got back into contention thereafter. A post race veterinary examination was carried out which revealed no injuries.

THOMAS WILLIAM (5) - brushed DAPPER RAPPER at the start. Squeezed CLASSIC RAPPER shortly after the start. Bumped nearing the end. Tightened DIAMOND GEEZER entering the bend. Checked off heels nearing the winning post, bumping BIGTIME FRED as a result.
DAPPER RAPPER (6) - brushed THOMAS WILLIAM at the start.
MAINLINE LIL (7) - bumped THOMAS WILLIAM nearing the bend. Bumped BIGTIME FRED from behind entering the bend. Raced wide through the early stages of the home straight.
BIGTIME FRED (8) - bumped from behind entering the bend. Bumped nearing the winning post.
